48	/**
49	 * A resequencer that re-orders a (continuous) stream of {@link Exchange}s. The algorithm implemented by
50	 * {@link ResequencerEngine} is based on the detection of gaps in a message stream rather than on a fixed batch size.
51	 * Gap detection in combination with timeouts removes the constraint of having to know the number of messages of a
52	 * sequence (i.e. the batch size) in advance.
53	 * <p>
54	 * Messages must contain a unique sequence number for which a predecessor and a successor is known. For example a
55	 * message with the sequence number 3 has a predecessor message with the sequence number 2 and a successor message with
56	 * the sequence number 4. The message sequence 2,3,5 has a gap because the successor of 3 is missing. The resequencer
57	 * therefore has to retain message 5 until message 4 arrives (or a timeout occurs).
58	 * <p>
59	 * Instances of this class poll for {@link Exchange}s from a given <code>endpoint</code>. Resequencing work and the
60	 * delivery of messages to the next <code>processor</code> is done within the single polling thread.
61	 *
62	 * @see ResequencerEngine
63	 */
64	public class StreamResequencer extends BaseProcessorSupport
65	        implements SequenceSender<Exchange>, Navigate<Processor>, Traceable, IdAware, RouteIdAware, StepIdAware {
66	
