118	     * Returns this resequencer's capacity. The capacity is the maximum number of exchanges that can be managed by this
119	     * resequencer at a given point in time. If the capacity if reached, polling from the endpoint will be skipped for
120	     * <code>timeout</code> milliseconds giving exchanges the possibility to time out and to be delivered after the
121	     * waiting period.
122	     *
123	     * @return this resequencer's capacity.
124	     */
125	    public int getCapacity() {
126	        return capacity;
127	    }
